As mention by Nick, you can also use the Parallel.ForEach method to accomplish the same thing.

Example:

    Parallel.ForEach (Arr,
        new ParallelOptions { MaxDegreeOfParallelism = maxConcurrency },
        (x) =&gt; { print(x); } );

